This paper focuses on a dataset for testing generative commonsense reasoning, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of sequence generation methods, which falls under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the dataset includes descriptions of natural scenes, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
